{"data": [{"id": "4742640", "title": "Why Gold Could Rally In 2025 Despite Recent Weakness", "description": "<p></p> <p>The price of gold has been one of the best-performing commodities, year to date. Hussein Allidina, Managing Director and Head of Commodities at TD Asset Management, explains why he sees the precious metal pushing even higher into the new year.</p> <h2>Transcript</h2> <p><strong>Greg Bonnell:</strong> Gold has pulled back from its record highs in the wake of the US election. But are there still catalysts that could push the precious metal higher in 2025?</p> <p>Joining us now to discuss, Hussein Allidina, Managing Director and Head of Commodities with TD Asset Management. Hussein, always good to have you on the program.</p> <p><strong>Hussein Allidina:</strong> Thanks for having me, Greg.</p> <p><strong>Greg Bonnell:</strong> Interesting year for gold. You and I have had many discussions about gold this year. We have seen the pullback. Walk us through what we have seen. Why are we at this position right now with gold?</p> <p><strong>Hussein Allidina:</strong> Yeah. Gold has reached many nominal highs this year. We did pull back following the election in the US on the strength in the dollar. I ultimately think that gold does move higher over the course of 2025, 2026.</p> <p>And structurally-- we've talked about this before-- if we look at central banks in the emerging market, they hold a lot of fiat currency, especially relative to their peers in the OECD. If you look at gold holdings in the US, Germany, and France, etc., they're materially higher as a percentage of their reserves relative to the fiat that they hold.</p> <p>If we look in the emerging market, most of their reserves are in US dollars, euros, IMF special drawing rights. And we have seen a diversification out of that paper, frankly, into gold. And I don't think that changes. I think it takes multiple years to get to the levels that you see in the OECD. So that structural demand for gold, I think, will</p>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742640-why-gold-could-rally-2025-despite-recent-weakness", "pub_date": "2024-12-06 17:55:00"}, {"id": "4742622", "title": "Why Is The Jobs Report So Important?", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/912016096/image_912016096.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Businesspeople carrying boxes around on painted lanes on asphalt\" data-id=\"912016096\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/912016096/image_912016096.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/912016096/image_912016096.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/912016096/image_912016096.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/912016096/image_912016096.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/912016096/image_912016096.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/912016096/image_912016096.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/912016096/image_912016096.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/912016096/image_912016096.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">Klaus Vedfelt</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>The bull run into year-end took a break yesterday for no reason other than investors must be gasping for air at the elevated altitude of 6,000 for the S&amp;P 500 and 45,000 for the Dow Jones Industrial Average. Except</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/912016096/image_912016096.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742622-why-is-the-jobs-report-so-important", "pub_date": "2024-12-06 17:50:38"}, {"id": "4742637", "title": "VanEck Crypto Monthly Recap For November 2024", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1419599523/image_1419599523.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Making Money in the Meta verse\" data-id=\"1419599523\" data-type=\"getty-image\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"></p> <p class=\"item-credits\">We Are</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p><em>November sparked a crypto revival with Trump\u2019s pro-crypto cabinet picks. Ethereum revealed faster block times and quantum-resistant upgrades, while Solana set revenue records amid memecoin mania.</em></p> <p><em>Please note that VanEck may have a position(s) in the digital asset(s) described</em></p>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742637-vaneck-crypto-monthly-recap-for-november-2024", "pub_date": "2024-12-06 17:46:00"}, {"id": "4742615", "title": "Intel: The Problems Gelsinger Leaves Behind", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1670843479/image_1670843479.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Intel headquarters in Santa Clara, California, USA\" data-id=\"1670843479\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1670843479/image_1670843479.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1670843479/image_1670843479.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1670843479/image_1670843479.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1670843479/image_1670843479.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1670843479/image_1670843479.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1670843479/image_1670843479.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1670843479/image_1670843479.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1670843479/image_1670843479.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">JHVEPhoto</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>The sudden departure of Intel (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/INTC\" title=\"Intel Corporation\">INTC</a></span>) CEO Pat Gelsinger this week laid bare the myriad problems that Intel faces. Of these, the most pressing are the lagging efforts to regain semiconductor process leadership as well as contending with Nvidia\u2019s (</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1670843479/image_1670843479.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742615-intel-problems-gelsinger-leaves-behind", "pub_date": "2024-12-06 17:35:26"}, {"id": "4742613", "title": "Why CrowdStrike Still Has More Room To Run", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/147456329/image_147456329.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"IT Engineer in Action Configuring Servers\" data-id=\"147456329\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1022px\" srcset=